    <img src="/img/about/steven-krams.jpg" alt="Steven H. Krams, President and Chairman of Magna-Tech Electronic Co." class="portrait-photo">
    <p>{{ company.history }}</p>

    <p>
      Magna-Tech's early business built sound recording, playback, and copying equipment for
      motion picture studios, working with nearly every major Hollywood and international studio
      over the decades. The company has received two Scientific/Technical Academy Awards for
      engineering contributions to motion picture sound — see <a href="/about/awards/">Awards</a>
      for the specific citations.
    </p>

    <p>
      Since the shift to digital cinema, MTE has focused on total design engineering for image and
      sound systems: professional AV equipment, design, and fit-out for cinema theaters, conference
      rooms, museums, planetariums, educational facilities, and government and military institutions,
      across both analog and digital systems.
    </p>

    <h2 style="clear:both;">Where We Work</h2>
    <p>MTE and its office, agent, and partner network reach:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>United States (shipping worldwide) and Canada</li>
      <li>United Kingdom</li>
      <li>Lebanon, UAE, Jordan, Egypt (Middle East)</li>
      <li>Saudi Arabia and Bahrain</li>
      <li>Brazil, Argentina, and other Latin American markets</li>
      <li>India</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-muted">
      MTE Russia operates independently as our partner for the Russian-speaking market — see
      <a href="{{ company.domains.partnerRu }}">magna-tech.org</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What We Design and Supply For</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Movie theaters, live theaters, and cultural centers</li>
      <li>Museums and planetariums</li>
      <li>Educational establishments</li>
      <li>Shopping centers and retail environments</li>
      <li>Stadiums and sports arenas</li>
      <li>Houses of worship</li>
      <li>Hotels and recreational centers</li>
      <li>Cruise ships</li>
      <li>Government and military facilities</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Work</h2>
    <p>
      As an independent systems integrator, we build our relationships with customers and partners
      on mutual trust and transparent business processes, and we try to give large and small clients
      the same level of attention. Our team draws on specialists across different disciplines and
      countries so we can deliver turnkey projects and take on complex problems.
    </p>

